<TITLE> Fomer nat'l hockey player Jashimuddin passes away </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 6 (bdnews24.com) - Former national hockey player Jashimuddin Ahmed Kanchan died of cardiac arrest in the early hours of Monday at the age of 43. Kanchan, also a former executive member of the Bangladesh Hockey Federation, left behind his wife, a son, a daughter and a host of well-wishers. He fell sick on Sunday night and breathed his last on way to hospital at 3:00pm, said family sources. His first namaz-e-janaza was held at the Moulana Bhasani National Hockey Stadium with a large number of well-wishers attending the janaza. Later, his second namaz-e-janaza was held at the Abahani Limited ground before he was laid to rest at the Azimpur graveyard. Kanchan started his career at Mohammedan Sporting Club (1982-1984) and later joined Abahani Limited (1985-88), Ajax Sporting Club (1989-91) and Dhaka Mariners Club (1992-94). The midfielder represented Bangladesh from 1985 to 1989 after being picked for the junior national side in 1984. Different organisations and clubs condoled the death of one of Bangladesh's most dependable left halves. Bangladesh Olympic Association (BOA), Bangladesh Hockey Federation, Bangladesh Football Federation, Bangladesh Sports Journalists Association (BSJA), Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB), Bangladesh Handball Federation (BHF), Mariners Young Club, Mohammedan Sporting Club, Abahani Limited, Dhaka Veterans Hockey Players Association expressed deep shock on Monday. Abahani Club have arranged a qulkhwani on Thursday after Asr prayers at 4:30 pm on the club premises while the Hockey Federation will hold the qul on Saturday next. bd
